## ✅ Implementation Summary

- **Users table**: Added to Drizzle schema with all required columns (id, githubId, email, name, avatarUrl, createdAt)
- **Migration**: Generated `drizzle/0002_strong_gressill.sql` that will auto-apply when API routes are called
- **NextAuth signIn callback**: Implemented upsert logic - creates user on first login, updates name/avatar on subsequent logins  
- **NextAuth session callback**: Added userId to JWT token and passes it through to session object
- **TypeScript types**: Extended session interface to include userId
- **Quality gates**: Both `npx tsc --noEmit` and `npx vitest run` pass successfully

## Key Implementation Details

The solution follows established codebase patterns:
- Uses `uuid()` for ID generation like other entities
- Leverages the existing `runMigrations()` pattern that auto-applies migrations in API routes
- Implements proper error handling and type safety in NextAuth callbacks
- Maintains JWT session strategy compatible with SQLite architecture

The users table is now ready to support user-scoped projects in the next user story (US-003). All GitHub OAuth users will have their identity persisted in the database with their session including both githubId and internal userId for database operations.

